         <component>
            <section ID="ID35">
               <id root="e3bf1975-fac6-4c90-9534-c25c4165f35d"/>
               <code code="34088-5" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="OVERDOSAGE SECTION"/>
               <title>OVERDOSAGE</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph ID="ID36">Topically applied corticosteroids can be absorbed in sufficient amounts to produce systemic effects (See<content styleCode="bold"> <linkHtml href="#ID15">PRECAUTIONS</linkHtml>
                     </content>).</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20170117"/>
            </section>
         </component>
         <component>
            <section ID="ID37">
               <id root="153b4da1-4a7b-4aa4-b910-67ee71fefd4c"/>
               <code code="34068-7" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DOSAGE &amp; ADMINISTRATION SECTION"/>
               <title>DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph ID="ID38">Topical corticosteroids are generally applied to the affected area as a thin film from three to four times daily depending on the severity of the condition.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Occlusive dressings may be used for the management of psoriasis or recalcitrant conditions.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>If an infection develops, the use of occlusive dressings should be discontinued and appropriate antimicrobial therapy instituted.</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20170117"/>
            </section>
         </component>
